comments.body:
We are actually working through some of this now for a locked down buildah container.   

@TomSweeneyRedHat Could you contribute the Dockerfile we have so far for building this?

The problem, I see is do we just go with strickly a locked down BuildahCtr or do we also go with a flexible Buildah container.

I always wanted to tell people multiple different ways you can run buildah inside of a container on top of CRI-O, Docker and Podman.

Getting this right and putting one or two buildahctrs out on quay.io seems like the right thing to do.

@TomSweeneyRedHat Can we get a quay.io/buildah/ repository?
